# india-markets MCP — Architecture

MCP server for Indian financial market analysis. Claude calls tools defined
here to fetch live data. No web UI or REST API.

## Built Layers

| # | Layer | File | What it does |
|---|-------|------|-------------|
| 1 | Market Foundation | `tools/kite_tools.py` | Live quotes, OHLC candles, indices (Kite Connect) |
| 2 | Institutional Flows | `tools/nse_tools.py` | FII/DII cash flows, participant-wise F&O OI (NSE public) |
| 3 | Derivatives | `tools/derivatives_tools.py` | Option chain, PCR, max pain, OI walls, India VIX |
| 4 | Global Macro | `tools/macro_tools.py` | Global indices, crude, gold, DXY, USD/INR, US yields (yfinance) |
| 5 | News & Sentiment | `tools/news_tools.py` | RSS feeds + Google News, event-risk detection |
| 6 | Signal Scoring | `core/signal_scorer.py` + `tools/signal_tools.py` | Market-level composite: multi-day regime detection (CORRECTION + enhanced EXODUS/FEAR), signal agreement multiplier, conflict flags, weighted score |
| 7 | Technical Analysis | `tools/technicals_tools.py` | 20/50/200 DMA, RSI, Bollinger, MACD, support/resistance, relative strength vs Nifty |
| 8 | Stock Fundamentals | `tools/fundamentals_tools.py` + `core/fundamentals_client.py` | Valuation, growth, profitability, financial health via yfinance |

**Daily snapshots** — `scripts/save_daily_snapshot.py` runs at 7 PM IST via cron.
Saves full market state to `data/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.json`. 61+ snapshots accumulated
(Dec 2025 → present). Backfill script: `scripts/backfill_history.py`.

## Key Decisions

- **MCP over REST API** — developer uses Cursor daily; no separate UI needed
- **Zerodha Kite Connect** — primary data source (paid, most reliable for NSE)
- **NSE public scraping** — FII/DII flows via `nsepython` (free, no auth)
- **No portfolio tracking** — pure market analysis tool
- **Selective context injection** — Claude decides which tools to call per question
- **Signal scoring** — raw data → directional scores (-1 to +1) before Claude synthesizes
- **Access token is manual** — Kite token expires daily, user provides it in `.env`

## Directory Layout

```
core/          ← HTTP sessions, auth, instrument caches, signal scoring, daily store
tools/         ← Business logic and derived signals (no MCP imports)
server/app.py  ← MCP server: @mcp.tool() wrappers + system prompt instructions
scripts/       ← Cron jobs, backfill, one-off utilities
data/daily/    ← Daily JSON snapshots (gitignored; .gitkeep tracked)
```

Run via `.mcp.json`: `python -m server.app` — the `-m` flag adds the project root to
`sys.path` so all `from core.x` and `from tools.x` imports work.

