## Signal Scoring Improvements (Layer 6 Phase 2)

Targeted fixes to the existing market-level scorer. Each is independent.

| ID | Fix | Impact | Detail |
|----|-----|--------|--------|
| S1 | Signal agreement multiplier | High | ✅ **DONE** — When ≥3 layers agree on direction, multiply composite by 1.3× (capped at ±1.0). `compute_composite()` now returns dict with agreement metadata. |
| S2 | VIX rate-of-change trigger | High | ✅ **DONE** — `vix_change_pct > 10%` as alternate FEAR trigger, even below VIX 22 absolute threshold. Also: VIX 3-day RoC > 25% triggers FEAR (part of A3). |
| S3 | Event calendar overrides | Medium | Static calendar in `core/event_calendar.py` — RBI MPC, F&O monthly expiry, Budget, FOMC. Hard weight overrides on event days. |
| S4 | News catalyst concentration | Medium | When event_risk ≥ 8 and headlines share a theme, auto-bump news weight. |
| S5 | BankNifty brief | Low | Add optional `underlying` param to `market_brief()` for BankNifty/FinNifty. |
| S6 | Expiry week auto-detection | Low | Monthly vs weekly expiry → adjust derivatives weight (monthly has stronger max pain gravity). |

### Minor cleanup (fix when touching nearby code)

- `score_vix()` maps VIX < 10 → +0.5; consider flattening to +0.25 (complacency)
- System prompt "Derivatives +20%" is ambiguous — clarify as percentage points
- `macro_client.py` caches error responses for 60s — consider shorter TTL on errors

